<item>
            <title>[LU-2972] Execution conflict of OFED initialisation script</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2972</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to initialization failure of the infiniband interface for external OFED builds (ofa) a change (&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5630&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5630&lt;/a&gt;) has been created, to add the (boot) initialization script provided by the OFED software to the kernel-ib RPM again. The problem is documented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2907&quot; title=&quot;Infiniband HW kernel modules of OFA builds not started at system boot&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2907&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2907&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The distribution package &apos;rdma-3.6-1.el6.noarch&apos; provides an initialization script to configure the infiniband interface, too. This might lead to conflicts during the system boot/shutdown phase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please investigate whether both scripts can be installed and operate without problems.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="17911">LU-2972</key>
            <summary>Execution conflict of OFED initialisation script</summary>
