                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="56700" author="heckes" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2013 16:14:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Problem is obsolete since the startup of mlx4 kernel modules is handled by the rdma init script now (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2907&quot; title=&quot;Infiniband HW kernel modules of OFA builds not started at system boot&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2907&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2907&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) correctly again. The openibd init script is removed from the packaging list of the ofa (OFED) RPM at build time. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
